intro¶

In this notebook we are going to define the most important functions for dealing with the data. As I used prod.gy for labeling and drawing boxes I need to convert the encoded pics to real pics with the coordinates of the bounding box.

path_sample_data = 'test_data/sample.jsonl'
data = []
with open(path_sample_data) as f:
    for line in f:
        data.append(json.loads(line))
        
data = re.sub('^data:image/.+;base64,', '', data[0]['image'])
